Cape Town â€“ Another child has been killed in the Western Cape. An 18-month-old baby boy died after he was brought in for medical attention at a health facility in Kensington, Cape Town. It's reported that the boy sustained serious injuries to his head and body. According to police, healthworkers contacted them and the child's 26-year-old stepfather was arrested and his 30-year-old mother taken in for questioning. The suspect will appear in the Cape Town Magistrate's Court once charged, police spokesperson Noloyiso Rwexana said. This is a developing story. IOL